# Project Structure Guide

This project is a Next.js v15 application. Its core goal is to sync SeoBot generated articles, accessed via API, to the database for optimized SEO content management.

- `app/`: Main application code, including pages, layouts, and API routes
- `lib/`: Shared utilities (e.g., [prisma.js](mdc:lib/prisma.js) for database, [GCS.js](mdc:lib/GCS.js) for Google Cloud Storage)
- `prisma/`: Prisma schema and migrations
- `config/`: Configuration files
- `public/`: Static assets

Key configuration files:
- [next.config.mjs](mdc:next.config.mjs): Next.js config
- [tailwind.config.mjs](mdc:tailwind.config.mjs): Tailwind CSS config
- [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs): PostCSS config
- [jsconfig.json](mdc:jsconfig.json): JS config
